1
00:00:30,063 --> 00:00:34,938
"Wooju Bakery"

2
00:00:41,188 --> 00:00:45,355
What do you call that thing we were just
on?

3
00:00:46,438 --> 00:00:47,730
This?

4
00:00:47,855 --> 00:00:50,813
I'm not sure what it's called either.

5
00:00:50,938 --> 00:00:52,355
It's actually pretty amazing.

6
00:00:53,022 --> 00:00:54,980
Oh, you mean a swing?

7
00:00:55,105 --> 00:00:55,897
A swing!

8
00:00:57,063 --> 00:00:58,563
Swings are so much fun.

9
00:01:00,022 --> 00:01:01,188
Oh!

10
00:01:01,522 --> 00:01:04,522
Your Highness, I'm sorry!

11
00:01:04,897 --> 00:01:06,188
Get up.

12
00:01:07,563 --> 00:01:09,355
I'm the reason Hachi got arrested.

13
00:01:09,480 --> 00:01:12,272
What do you mean he got caught because of
you?

14
00:01:12,397 --> 00:01:13,938
The police got him

15
00:01:14,063 --> 00:01:15,855
when I wasn't paying attention.

16
00:01:15,980 --> 00:01:17,438
Let's go check on him first.

17
00:01:17,897 --> 00:01:19,063
Thankfully…

18
00:01:19,188 --> 00:01:21,188
- Huh?
- He got away…

19
00:01:23,105 --> 00:01:25,188
- He's here.
- Huh?

20
00:01:25,313 --> 00:01:28,230
Why didn't you say so sooner? You scared
me to death!

21
00:01:28,355 --> 00:01:29,272
Your Highness…

22
00:01:29,397 --> 00:01:31,480
Please don't send him to jail!

23
00:01:32,022 --> 00:01:34,188
Hachi! Hands up!

24
00:01:36,272 --> 00:01:37,688
Hands down.

25
00:01:39,063 --> 00:01:41,813
Hey! Are you a dog? Are you?

26
00:01:41,938 --> 00:01:43,022
Why are you eating dog food?

27
00:01:43,147 --> 00:01:45,730
Because… I can't resist the smell of it.

28
00:01:46,188 --> 00:01:48,313
Ugh…

29
00:01:48,438 --> 00:01:50,188
I'm speechless… Hey!

30
00:01:50,313 --> 00:01:52,730
If word gets out that I'm feeding my
bakery staff dog food,

31
00:01:52,855 --> 00:01:54,230
that I'm some kind of sweatshop owner,

32
00:01:54,355 --> 00:01:55,647
what am I supposed to do?

33
00:01:55,772 --> 00:01:58,480
- Huh?
- Aren't you already a sweatshop owner?

34
00:01:58,772 --> 00:02:01,147
Seriously… How am I a sweatshop owner?

35
00:02:01,272 --> 00:02:02,647
You haven't paid our wages, have you?

36
00:02:02,772 --> 00:02:06,522
Oh, really? I knew you'd say that.

37
00:02:06,647 --> 00:02:08,147
Look, read the contract!

38
00:02:08,272 --> 00:02:11,730
You signed it yourself!

39
00:02:12,938 --> 00:02:14,938
It's not that I'm not paying you.

40
00:02:15,063 --> 00:02:18,355
You guys caused trouble, and now you're
working off your debt!

41
00:02:18,480 --> 00:02:19,272
Hmph.

42
00:02:20,772 --> 00:02:22,105
Tsk!

43
00:02:37,647 --> 00:02:39,313
Um… Senior?

44
00:02:39,438 --> 00:02:40,022
Yeah?

45
00:02:40,147 --> 00:02:41,480
That Wooju Bakery over there.

46
00:02:41,605 --> 00:02:44,272
What now? Are you going to talk about
aliens again?

47
00:02:45,063 --> 00:02:46,522
No, no.

48
00:02:46,980 --> 00:02:48,397
Is their bread… any good?

49
00:02:48,522 --> 00:02:49,438
Why?

50
00:02:49,563 --> 00:02:51,063
Did someone say it wasn't good?

51
00:02:51,188 --> 00:02:53,022
No, no, that's not it.

52
00:02:53,897 --> 00:02:56,105
Among the staff there,

53
00:02:56,230 --> 00:03:00,438
is there anyone who carries around some
kind of weird gun?

54
00:03:00,563 --> 00:03:01,855
A gun?

55
00:03:05,355 --> 00:03:05,730
What kind of gun?

56
00:03:05,855 --> 00:03:07,272
No, I just…

57
00:03:07,397 --> 00:03:10,563
I think I might have been hit by some
weird gun.

58
00:03:10,688 --> 00:03:14,355
Maybe I was, maybe I wasn't… was I?

59
00:03:14,480 --> 00:03:16,813
Did you finish handling that complaint
from yesterday?

60
00:03:16,938 --> 00:03:17,855
Yes…

61
00:03:17,980 --> 00:03:19,605
I have to go, I've got things to do.

62
00:03:20,397 --> 00:03:21,772
Good work.

63
00:03:23,480 --> 00:03:25,980
It's suspicious no matter how I look at
it.

64
00:03:26,480 --> 00:03:28,855
Ugh… But how am I supposed to prove it?

65
00:03:28,980 --> 00:03:30,938
That jerk… Wooju Bakery…

66
00:03:31,063 --> 00:03:34,063
Mina… Dragon Palace Restaurant… Jirol…

67
00:03:34,272 --> 00:03:38,355
Wait, wasn't Jirol already suspicious
before the bakery even opened?

68
00:03:38,480 --> 00:03:39,730
He looks so dim-witted.

69
00:03:39,855 --> 00:03:41,897
Could he be hiding the fact that he's an
evil alien?

70
00:03:42,022 --> 00:03:43,055
Is he putting on an act?

71
00:03:44,105 --> 00:03:45,272
I'm back!

72
00:03:45,397 --> 00:03:47,647
Come here for a second.

73
00:03:47,772 --> 00:03:50,605
You were only delivering nearby, why did
it take you so long?

74
00:03:50,730 --> 00:03:51,730
- Ouch…
- Why are you so late?

75
00:03:51,855 --> 00:03:53,313
I thought something happened to you!

76
00:03:53,438 --> 00:03:54,980
No, how could I possibly get into trouble?

77
00:03:55,105 --> 00:03:57,355
I'm the best delivery guy in this
neighborhood.

78
00:03:57,480 --> 00:03:58,272
Cut the crap.

79
00:03:58,397 --> 00:04:02,230
All you do is dance and mess around with
those kids all day.

80
00:04:02,355 --> 00:04:03,105
That's not it.

81
00:04:03,230 --> 00:04:05,397
I'm doing it for the future customers of
Dragon Palace.

82
00:04:05,522 --> 00:04:07,772
I'm helping to attract customers, right?

83
00:04:07,897 --> 00:04:11,188
Enough. I'll give you one more chance. If
you drag your feet again,

84
00:04:11,313 --> 00:04:12,938
I'm firing you, you hear me?

85
00:04:13,063 --> 00:04:14,230
Yes…

86
00:04:14,355 --> 00:04:15,647
Can you come out for a second? I have
something to tell you.

87
00:04:15,772 --> 00:04:18,147
Officer… I didn't do anything wrong.

88
00:04:18,563 --> 00:04:21,397
No, boss, it's not like that… I…

89
00:04:21,522 --> 00:04:22,980
I came here because I know everything!

90
00:04:23,105 --> 00:04:25,397
What exactly do you know? Seriously.

91
00:04:25,730 --> 00:04:27,022
Aliens!

92
00:04:27,938 --> 00:04:29,397
You're one, aren't you?

93
00:04:31,605 --> 00:04:33,063
No, I…

94
00:04:33,188 --> 00:04:34,397
You really…

95
00:04:34,688 --> 00:04:35,730
What aliens?

96
00:04:35,855 --> 00:04:37,647
What are you even talking about?

97
00:04:37,772 --> 00:04:39,230
I'm not one.

98
00:04:40,063 --> 00:04:41,397
I'm a person who even have an ID card, you
know.

99
00:04:41,522 --> 00:04:44,522
Then why did you kidnap the YouTuber Mina
last time?

100
00:04:46,188 --> 00:04:47,605
That was…

101
00:04:48,688 --> 00:04:50,355
Rather than a kidnapping, it was more
like…

102
00:04:50,480 --> 00:04:52,355
If you tell me the truth,

103
00:04:52,480 --> 00:04:54,480
I might go easy on you.

104
00:04:54,605 --> 00:04:56,980
I'm really not an alien, okay?

105
00:05:00,855 --> 00:05:02,647
Actually, the alien…

106
00:05:05,063 --> 00:05:07,397
is a guy named Chairman Lee.

107
00:05:11,397 --> 00:05:12,397
Chairman Lee?

108
00:05:12,522 --> 00:05:14,855
He's truly despicable!

109
00:05:16,772 --> 00:05:18,105
Despicable?

110
00:05:20,272 --> 00:05:21,355
Despicable?

111
00:05:21,480 --> 00:05:22,688
Yeah! Exactly.

112
00:05:22,813 --> 00:05:26,230
He's the kind of guy who came here to
destroy the Earth, seriously.

113
00:05:27,105 --> 00:05:28,605
But…

114
00:05:29,147 --> 00:05:33,022
You can't tell anyone I told you, okay?

115
00:05:33,605 --> 00:05:37,105
Tell me more clearly, I can go easy on
you…

116
00:05:39,438 --> 00:05:42,813
Wooju Bakery, no bias, no hype, just an
honest review.

117
00:05:42,938 --> 00:05:44,105
If you go to Wooju Bakery,

118
00:05:44,230 --> 00:05:46,272
You really have to choose your bread
carefully…

119
00:05:46,397 --> 00:05:47,688
Damn it.

120
00:05:50,022 --> 00:05:53,063
I don't want to just stand by and watch
the shop turn into a mess.

121
00:05:55,980 --> 00:05:59,063
The boss hasn't even woken up yet, and
we've already cleaned the whole shop.

122
00:06:00,897 --> 00:06:03,813
That's not what I'm talking about! I mean…

123
00:06:03,938 --> 00:06:07,647
A bakery is supposed to smell like fresh,
delicious bread.

124
00:06:07,772 --> 00:06:12,688
And there should be customers quietly
coming in to buy bread.

125
00:06:12,813 --> 00:06:15,438
Right now, it's just noisy and chaotic,
isn't it?

126
00:06:15,563 --> 00:06:19,397
But the customers love it…

127
00:06:19,522 --> 00:06:20,938
Quiet!

128
00:06:21,480 --> 00:06:22,980
The boss is talking.

129
00:06:24,938 --> 00:06:30,730
Get rid of all those questionable breads
and start over.

130
00:06:31,355 --> 00:06:32,772
But…

131
00:06:33,188 --> 00:06:35,230
The bread you make…

132
00:06:35,355 --> 00:06:36,647
What about it?

133
00:06:36,772 --> 00:06:38,230
It's really bad.

134
00:06:38,355 --> 00:06:40,313
This is the place, right?

135
00:06:43,522 --> 00:06:45,188
Please wait a moment…

136
00:06:48,105 --> 00:06:48,980
Try them all.

137
00:06:49,105 --> 00:06:51,730
- They look so delicious.
- Those ones too.

138
00:07:04,147 --> 00:07:07,105
Boss, look over here.

139
00:07:07,230 --> 00:07:09,772
Only the bread you made hasn't sold.

140
00:07:11,397 --> 00:07:12,230
So annoying.

141
00:07:12,355 --> 00:07:13,855
This bakery, even the bread is weird.

142
00:07:13,980 --> 00:07:17,022
The drinks are weird, the staff is weird,
everything is weird.

143
00:07:19,105 --> 00:07:21,438
The customers are the weirdest ones!

144
00:07:31,230 --> 00:07:32,772
Scream!

145
00:07:36,855 --> 00:07:38,022
Air!

146
00:07:38,688 --> 00:07:40,105
Shut your mouth.

147
00:08:13,522 --> 00:08:15,147
Why are you up so early?

148
00:08:16,480 --> 00:08:20,605
Hey! Stop making noise and go back to
sleep.

149
00:08:20,730 --> 00:08:23,772
The boss's bread isn't popular, so I'll
make some.

150
00:08:24,272 --> 00:08:25,647
I told you to go back to sleep.

151
00:08:31,105 --> 00:08:33,855
I said go back to sleep, are you deaf?

152
00:09:14,022 --> 00:09:15,397
Hmm~

153
00:09:16,063 --> 00:09:17,938
The bread smells really good.

154
00:09:23,355 --> 00:09:25,272
Why are you making that face?

155
00:09:26,730 --> 00:09:30,605
Or… did I do something wrong?

156
00:09:31,313 --> 00:09:32,772
No.

157
00:09:33,647 --> 00:09:38,063
Are you mad because I didn't help?

158
00:09:38,980 --> 00:09:40,938
I said it's not like that.

159
00:09:51,563 --> 00:09:53,730
I said it's not like that, can't you
understand?

160
00:09:54,397 --> 00:09:57,897
Alright, stop it.

161
00:09:58,022 --> 00:09:59,397
It's not because of you.

162
00:10:00,230 --> 00:10:03,605
Then what is it?

163
00:10:08,480 --> 00:10:11,230
The smell of the bread baking right now…
do you like it?

164
00:10:18,647 --> 00:10:19,980
Yeah.

165
00:10:24,605 --> 00:10:25,897
When I was little,

166
00:10:26,855 --> 00:10:29,855
I always loved the smell when my dad made
bread.

167
00:10:29,980 --> 00:10:33,938
I really want to smell that again.

168
00:10:34,063 --> 00:10:40,230
But now, I can't sense anything…

169
00:11:22,147 --> 00:11:25,022
Wow~ the bread smells so good.

170
00:11:25,147 --> 00:11:26,438
Hyung.

171
00:11:26,563 --> 00:11:28,313
Why are you here so early?

172
00:11:29,605 --> 00:11:34,147
I thought I'd bring some of your bread to
share at the station.

173
00:11:34,272 --> 00:11:36,230
After all, you just opened recently.

174
00:11:36,355 --> 00:11:37,730
Yeah.

175
00:11:38,105 --> 00:11:39,563
Our bread doesn't need promotion.

176
00:11:39,688 --> 00:11:41,438
Because it sells too well.

177
00:11:41,897 --> 00:11:43,980
Except for the bread Wooju makes.

178
00:11:44,605 --> 00:11:47,355
I specifically want to buy the bread Wooju
makes.

179
00:11:50,147 --> 00:11:52,522
The ones that just went into the oven need
a while.

180
00:11:54,355 --> 00:11:55,813
At least 10 minutes.

181
00:11:56,313 --> 00:11:59,272
Hmm? This one… I can just buy this one.

182
00:11:59,397 --> 00:12:01,688
Not that one… that one…

183
00:12:01,813 --> 00:12:02,980
That's from yesterday.

184
00:12:03,688 --> 00:12:05,772
It doesn't matter, I'll take this one.

185
00:12:06,772 --> 00:12:08,063
Uh…

186
00:12:11,522 --> 00:12:12,688
Yuck!

187
00:12:12,938 --> 00:12:15,730
This is terrible. You call this bread?

188
00:12:19,105 --> 00:12:20,480
No.

189
00:12:20,605 --> 00:12:23,022
Isn't it a bit harsh to say it's terrible
right to his face?

190
00:12:23,147 --> 00:12:26,813
A baker should know whether their bread is
good or not.

191
00:12:27,063 --> 00:12:28,313
Hey~

192
00:12:52,897 --> 00:12:56,563
Wooju, your sense of taste will come back.

193
00:12:56,980 --> 00:13:00,188
Didn't the doctor say it was only
temporary?

194
00:13:00,313 --> 00:13:02,438
Opening this bakery… it's really pushing
it.

195
00:13:02,563 --> 00:13:03,938
Boss.

196
00:13:05,105 --> 00:13:06,272
Hmm?

197
00:13:07,647 --> 00:13:09,563
Boss, don't worry.

198
00:13:13,313 --> 00:13:14,730
You've got me.

199
00:13:14,855 --> 00:13:16,063
What did you say?

200
00:13:17,313 --> 00:13:18,522
I'll teach you.

201
00:13:21,313 --> 00:13:22,813
How to bake bread!

202
00:13:24,480 --> 00:13:25,980
The best bread in the world.

203
00:13:29,438 --> 00:13:32,730
The best bread in the entire world?

204
00:13:34,355 --> 00:13:35,938
What are you talking about, you fraud?

205
00:13:36,063 --> 00:13:38,605
Why would I want to learn

206
00:13:39,438 --> 00:13:40,855
how to make your weird bread?

207
00:13:44,397 --> 00:13:45,897
Hey?

208
00:13:48,855 --> 00:13:50,230
Get out.

209
00:14:04,730 --> 00:14:05,980
Hey.

210
00:14:06,855 --> 00:14:09,647
Did you go to culinary school too?

211
00:14:09,772 --> 00:14:11,397
What makes you say that?

212
00:14:11,522 --> 00:14:15,272
Your technique… it's not bad.

213
00:14:15,397 --> 00:14:18,188
Do you want to give it a try?

214
00:14:25,772 --> 00:14:27,313
How do I do it?

215
00:14:44,147 --> 00:14:45,730
Take it slow.

216
00:15:00,938 --> 00:15:04,397
How's that? Doesn't it feel smoother?

217
00:15:04,522 --> 00:15:08,980
I've never seen anyone bake bread like
that before.

218
00:15:09,605 --> 00:15:11,272
Never?

219
00:15:13,105 --> 00:15:14,772
I doubt that.

220
00:15:14,897 --> 00:15:16,105
I don't remember clearly…

221
00:15:16,230 --> 00:15:21,063
But I think my dad used to bake bread just
like this.

222
00:15:22,980 --> 00:15:24,730
Think of your father.

223
00:15:26,522 --> 00:15:29,647
Imagine he's watching you right now.

224
00:15:30,813 --> 00:15:32,105
Yeah.

225
00:15:38,147 --> 00:15:39,772
Now, it's time for a taste test.

226
00:15:39,897 --> 00:15:41,397
Want to try it?

227
00:15:43,563 --> 00:15:44,563
Sigh.

228
00:15:44,688 --> 00:15:46,147
Raon…

229
00:15:46,272 --> 00:15:47,730
Yeah?

230
00:15:48,313 --> 00:15:55,313
Do you think I can really…

231
00:15:55,688 --> 00:15:58,397
Do you think I'll ever be able to taste
again?

232
00:16:04,272 --> 00:16:05,605
Yeah.

233
00:16:07,855 --> 00:16:09,397
That's good.

234
00:16:59,605 --> 00:17:01,147
Well?

235
00:17:03,397 --> 00:17:05,272
Can you taste anything?

236
00:20:34,022 --> 00:20:35,688
Stop it.

237
00:20:35,813 --> 00:20:37,897
Why not?

238
00:20:43,355 --> 00:20:45,813
Chairman Lee, about Mr. Kim from the
salvage shop…

239
00:20:45,938 --> 00:20:47,647
I can't shake this uneasy feeling.

240
00:20:47,772 --> 00:20:50,355
Are you sure it's okay to just let him go?

241
00:20:50,855 --> 00:20:53,397
That guy is a highly skilled engineer.

242
00:20:53,522 --> 00:20:56,647
They don't have a ship or any
communication gear anyway.

243
00:20:56,772 --> 00:21:01,063
If they want to go home, they'll have to
do exactly as we say.

244
00:21:01,813 --> 00:21:03,188
Chairman Lee.

245
00:21:03,313 --> 00:21:04,438
How have you been?

246
00:21:04,563 --> 00:21:06,563
Those people who crash-landed recently…

247
00:21:06,688 --> 00:21:08,105
They seem to be high-ranking officials.

248
00:21:08,230 --> 00:21:08,647
This…

249
00:21:08,772 --> 00:21:09,980
The news from off-world is blowing up.

250
00:21:10,105 --> 00:21:12,522
What? Tell me exactly who they are.

251
00:21:12,647 --> 00:21:15,605
They keep demanding the location of the
ship.

252
00:21:15,730 --> 00:21:19,438
But they won't reveal their identities or
where they're from.

253
00:21:20,688 --> 00:21:23,147
Find out where they are right now.

254
00:21:23,605 --> 00:21:24,480
And bring them to me immediately.

255
00:21:24,605 --> 00:21:26,480
Understood.

256
00:21:26,605 --> 00:21:29,022
If we keep this up, won't it cause trouble
later?

257
00:21:29,147 --> 00:21:30,522
It doesn't matter.

258
00:21:31,813 --> 00:21:34,147
We just need to catch them before that
happens.

259
00:21:34,272 --> 00:21:36,730
Understood.
